result.execSummary:
The defendant Brandon Gabelbauer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Brandon Gabelbauer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Brandon Gabelbauer was found guilty of 4th Degree Sexual Assault, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant must pay all outstanding fees and court obligations including costs of supervision during the term of probation.   If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

Defendant is not to have any contact, directly or indirectly, with the victim (person, property, residence or family). Any counseling deemed appropriate by agent. Defendant must submit a DNA specimen if required and pay for the testing. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on probation.

timeConds.notes: to be completed during the term of probation
